# Tutorials {.unnumbered}

People make mistakes. It is a common process in coding that everyone, no just beginners experience. Here we will provide some tips if you make a mistake and provide tutorials for some potential complicated concepts.

# Checklist

Since mistakes are regular, here is a checklist you should run through if your code is not working.

1.  Check Spelling

   - R is case sensitive! If you do not have a letter capitalized, misspell or anything of that source, double check. "Cats" is not the same as "cats" in R. If your code is not running, it could be because you are misspelling something!
